{"id":"tdsl-vbov","title":"Allow functions to provision turn budgets for action calls","description":"Functions cannot call costed actions (e.g. MeleeAttack with cost { attack }) because they lack access to the turn budget. This forces functions like resolve_action in osric_initiative.ttrpg to duplicate action logic by calling underlying mechanics directly instead of reusing existing actions.

Need a mechanism for functions to set up a turn budget before calling an action on behalf of a combatant. Possible approaches:
- A builtin like with_budget(entity, TurnBudget { attack: 1 }) { entity.MeleeAttack(...) }
- Implicit budget provisioning when a function calls a costed action
- A block-scoped turn budget declaration

This would let resolve_round call MeleeAttack/MissileAttack/Charge directly instead of reimplementing their logic.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tfgast@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-03T16:28:50Z","created_by":"Theodore Gast","updated_at":"2026-03-03T16:28:50Z"}

