{"id":"tdsl-1on5","title":"Warn when costed action fires on entity without provisioned budget","description":"When DeductCost fires for an entity that has no budget (or zero budget for the token), emit a diagnostic warning. This catches the common receiver-swap bug: with_budget(actor, { action: 1 }) { target.Attack(actor) } — where the DSL author swapped receiver and argument, causing the action to fire on target (who has no budget) instead of actor (who does).

This should be a general warning in the cost deduction pipeline, not specific to with_budget — any time turn_actor differs from the entity whose budget is being deducted, and the budget is absent or zero, a warning is warranted. Free actions (cost free or cost-less like TakeDamage) called on other entities are legitimate and should NOT warn.

The warning should surface as a diagnostic effect (not an error), giving the host/CLI visibility without breaking execution. Budget enforcement via RequiresCheck (tdsl-h2im) will separately cause the action to fail; this warning provides the 'why' to help the author find the bug.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"tfgast@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-03T17:31:40Z","created_by":"Theodore Gast","updated_at":"2026-03-03T17:31:40Z"}
